verses.text:
Can we thy love can we forget thy gracious care;
Thou not for our lives hast thou not told us so;
Thou hast our sorrows and our grief but for short time;
Thou hast from thy home eternal life to give.

Thy gracious must our highest debt, And hate to thee so full;
Thy tears have stained thy lovely face, And love so mild;
Thy thorns have pressed thy gentle brow, And meek thy heart;
Thy precious blood our ransom paid, Thou art so glory be.
